{"type":"message","id":"f82173b8","parentId":"2102d7fc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:10:53.186Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tb4citlgyrzt_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5137\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3150\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] analyze_tic.ps1\r\n[mutation proposed] analyze_tic.ps1\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 031017 - The TIC experiment requires analyzing pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns, but there's no existing script to parse and classify content across logs. Need to build the classifier infrastructure first.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"clear-ridge","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5137\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3150\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] analyze_tic.ps1\r\n[mutation proposed] analyze_tic.ps1\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 031017 - The TIC experiment requires analyzing pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns, but there's no existing script to parse and classify content across logs. Need to build the classifier infrastructure first.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774336253184}}
{"type":"message","id":"c05207e7","parentId":"f82173b8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:10:53.187Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tb4citlgyrzt_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 030813\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiments/tic_experiment.py (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Pending actions include:\r\n  - Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n  - Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n  - Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n  - Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe key next action from the \"Phase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" section is the TIC Experiment. This is the most concrete next step.\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist and implement the TIC classifier. I need to:\r\n1. Look at existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns\r\n3. Test prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me first check what files exist in the logs directory and look at a few pulse logs to understand the structure.\r\n\r\nSince I need to be specific and advance the goals, I'll:\r\n1. First examine the existing pulse logs to understand their format\r\n2. Create a TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier script\r\n\r\nLet me look at the state of the sandbox first - what pulse logs exist, what's their format.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\nLooking at the current state, the most concrete next action is implementing the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier to test the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. Let me examine existing pulse logs to understand their structure, then implement the classifier.\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight suggests causal structure IS invariant structure. The TIC experiment is the critical next step to validate this hypothesis against the success criteria (>70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nExamine existing pulse logs structure, then create TIC classifier implementation to test the invariance hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n\r\n## Purpose\r\nTest hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure. A compressor that finds \r\ninvariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Methodology\r\n1. **Invariant Detection**: Identify patterns that persist across multiple pulses\r\n2. **Variant Detection**: Identify patterns that change between pulses  \r\n3. **Prediction**: Use invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n4. **Validation**: Compare against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction)\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n### Phase 1: Pulse Log Analysis\r\n```python\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple\r\n\r\nPULSE_DIR = \"logs\"\r\nLOG_PATTERN = r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6})\\.md\"\r\n\r\ndef parse_pulse_log(filepath: str) -> Dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structured content from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    with open(filepath, 'r') as f:\r\n        content = f.read()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract sections\r\n    sections = {}\r\n    current_section = \"header\"\r\n    current_content = []\r\n    \r\n    for line in content.split('\\n'):\r\n        if line.startswith('## '):\r\n            if current_content:\r\n                sections[current_section] = '\\n'.join(current_content)\r\n            current_section = line[3:].lower()\r\n            current_content = []\r\n        else:\r\n            current_content.append(line)\r\n    \r\n    if current_content:\r\n        sections[current_section] = '\\n'.join(current_content)\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        'filepath': filepath,\r\n        'raw': content,\r\n        'sections': sections\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef get_pulse_sequence(n: int = 20) -> List[Dict]:\r\n    \"\"\"Get last n pulse logs sorted chronologically.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = []\r\n    for f in os.listdir(PULSE_DIR):\r\n        match = re.match(LOG_PATTERN, f)\r\n        if match:\r\n            filepath = os.path.join(PULSE_DIR, f)\r\n            logs.append((match.group(1), filepath))\r\n    \r\n    logs.sort(key=lambda x: x[0])\r\n    return [parse_pulse_log(path) for _, path in logs[-n:]]\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Phase 2: Invariant Extraction\r\n```python\r\nclass InvariantExtractor:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract invariant patterns from pulse sequence.\"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self, pulse_sequence: List[Dict]):\r\n        self.pulses = pulse_sequence\r\n        self.invariants = {}\r\n        self.variants = {}\r\n    \r\n    def extract_tokens(self, text: str) -> List[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Tokenize text into meaningful units.\"\"\"\r\n        # Extract words, code-like tokens, file paths\r\n        words = re.findall(r'\\b[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]+\\b', text.lower())\r\n        paths = re.findall(r'[\\w/]+\\.[a-zA-Z]+', text)\r\n        return list(set(words + paths))\r\n    \r\n    def compute_frequencies(self) -> Counter:\r\n        \"\"\"Count token occurrences across all pulses.\"\"\"\r\n        all_tokens = []\r\n        for pulse in self.pulses:\r\n            tokens = self.extract_tokens(pulse['raw'])\r\n            all_tokens.extend(tokens)\r\n        return Counter(all_tokens)\r\n    \r\n    def classify_invariants(self, min_pulse_ratio: float = 0.7) -> Tuple[Dict, Dict]:\r\n        \"\"\"Classify tokens as invariants (persistent) or variants (changing).\"\"\"\r\n        freq = self.compute_frequencies()\r\n        n_pulses = len(self.pulses)\r\n        threshold = min_pulse_ratio * n_pulses\r\n        \r\n        invariants = {token: count for token, count in freq.items() \r\n                      if count >= threshold}\r\n        variants = {token: count for token, count in freq.items() \r\n                    if count < threshold and count > 1}\r\n        \r\n        return invariants\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:08:50\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774336253186}}
